==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin ''sexaginta'', meaning "sixty"

===Noun===
'''sexagenarian''' (''plural'' '''sexagenarians''')

# A [[person]] who is 60 [[years]] old or between the [[ages]] of 60 and 69.

===Adjective===
'''sexagenary''' (''the noun as a modifier''; ''no [[comparative]] or [[superlative]]'')

# Being 60 years old or between the ages of 60 and 70.
# Of or relating to a sexagenarian.

